abstract: Dell will sell only two models of multimedia computers at Wal-Mart, the first step toward transforming its direct-sales strategy.
snippet: Dell will sell only two models of multimedia computers at Wal-Mart, the first step toward transforming its direct-sales strategy.
lead_paragraph: Dell, in a first step toward transforming its ailing strategy of selling direct to consumers, said yesterday that it planned to offer computers at Wal-Mart Stores, starting in June.

headline.main: Coming Soon to Wal-Mart: 2 Dell PCs
headline.print_headline: Coming Soon to Wal-Mart: 2 Low-End PCs From Dell
